author: alena lim
text: Very disappointing overall experience. Signed up through them (i.e., they're my home gym) back in Jan 2025 with a buddy and the 1/2 month discount was conveniently forgotten because of a 'system overwriting' for not just 1, 2 but 3 months (we were only awarded the discount in May 2025). Furthermore, with current promotions, the small gym has become crazily crowded during weekday evenings. You basically have to queue up for every machine. What a letdown to your loyal customers. Going to find a better gym elsewhere instead!

text: i was in the gym the other day and i felt that it was really not a good experience, the machine was rusty and the dumbbell was mismatched , some of the plate weight was also chipped off , only up side was that it had a variety of machines , compared to the other AF i been to, AF Bedok 537 i think? that was way better they have better machines and no rust and lighting was good as well , abit small but better than this, wouldn‚Äôt recommend

author: Lucien Lim
text:
Fully equipped gym, that‚Äôs clean and well maintained. I especially appreciated the friendly and welcoming staff. It‚Äôs located on the 3rd floor of Djitsun mall.

There are plastic dividers that separate the treadmills, allowing for privacy while running; also to limit Covid transmission.

author: Sara Hornseth-Bates
text: I have been a member of this gym from before they moved to this location, and have renewed every year because of the great service and facilities I have always received. The managers and other staff members are fantastic, friendly, helpful and knowledgeable. And the facilities are some of the best of the Anytime Fitnesses I've visited in Singapore. The gym is large and spacious, there is a wide variety of equipment that is well maintained and replaced as needed with newer models, and it is always clean and organised. I've never had any complaints, this is a great gym!

author: Lord Len
text:
I like the location as it‚Äôs easily accessible from home. Usually I use the cable machine at the quiet corner, but your ankle straps are always worn out. The velcros really cannot make it, they are torn or can no longer stick, and it seems that you still haven‚Äôt replaced them no matter how many times I returned to this gym. Please buy new ones üôèüèª. The other extensions that are very worn, please check and replace them too!

I understand that this gym has been existing for quite some time, hence the older machines. Other than the attachments being all worn out, I don‚Äôt really have much complaints. Thank you all!

author: Clemens Fink
text: This is definitely not my favourite gym in SG: Many machines are super old and only get replaced when they start falling apart. E.g. they got three different generations of treadmills there. No windows, no working wifi and no 5G connection either - so you‚Äôre really cut off from the rest of the world during your training. Would not recommend this gym.

text: Been through different outlets of AF, and I can only say that really like the vibes of this particular AF outlet. A vast selection of equipments and machines to target every specific muscle in the body, very serene interior and nevertheless, very warm-welcoming club staffs. Exercising is already a very strenuous activity, and we all know that what could make it worse, is an outlet that does not deliver the environmental factor. For that, I really give my deepest appreciation to the staff of AF Djitsun Mall Bedok because they really set the whole mood in this place for a better workout experience for everyone. Thank you once again for making this place so enjoyable. üëçüèªüôèüèºüôáüèº‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è

author: chong
text:
Gym was quite crowded due to ongoing promotion. Was doing a dumbell press halfway with my earphones on and suddenly a guy just passby and farted. Cb the rancid smell hit me like a truck, completely breaking my breathing rhythm and focus.

Worse yet, the distraction caused me to lose control of the weights, resulting in a strained shoulder as I tried to re-adjust mid-rep. Now I‚Äôm left dealing with pain because some clown couldn‚Äôt step outside or at least have basic decency.

If you‚Äôre going to pack the place with promotions, at least monitor behavior so people can work out safely.

author: Nazrul Haique
text: One of the better AF gyms. Quite a number of equipment and machines are available. Importantly, their staff are friendly and approachable. The only downside is one specific uncle in his early 40s (possibly a regular) who likes to make other gym-goers feel uncomfortable. He purposely flexes in front of others while they are working out and pretends to talk on his phone via earpiece, making loud remarks about how long he has been working out. I hope you guys look into this. Nonetheless, it‚Äôs a 5-star gym.

text: 2 years back, I was searching for a suitable gym as I needed to rehabilitate my knee after partial ACL tear in order to get back to playing football. AF Bedok hit all the right notes, with all the equipment that I needed for my glutes, quads and hamstrings. The fact that it's 24 hours is fantastic, as I could head over either after putting my kid to bed or wake up early and get some exercise in before work. Staff are friendly, and have done a great job creating a community and refreshing the gym now and again with little tweaks or new equipment. Keep up the great work!
